CITING FCMA

If you are using the Princeton Full Correlation Matrix Analysis (FCMA) Toolbox, please cite us.

This citation is for a conference poster; the associated paper is in press and will soon replace it.
Please see <http://princeton.edu/fcma> for updates.

Wang, Y., Li, K., Charikar, M., Cohen, J. D., & Turk-Browne, N. B. (May, 2013). What you find depends on how you look: Category selectivity in frontal cortex revealed by whole-brain correlation analysis. Poster presented at Vision Sciences Society, Naples, FL.